From: Octopus Orchestrator upstream PR draft wave (M0-18)
Subject: [PATCH] auto-reply: register /octo slash command in shared registry

Register /octo in buildBuiltinChatCommands() so the Octopus in-chat
operator surface (INTEGRATION.md §In-chat operator surface) is
dispatchable from every channel that consumes the shared registry.
The action choices enumerate the documented subcommands: status,
missions, mission, arms, arm, attach, unattach, tail, events, help.
target + captureRemaining value handle composite forms such as
'arm kill <id>' and 'mission create <template>'.

This change only adds the REGISTRATION entry. The handler lands in
a later octo-internal milestone at src/octo/cli/slash-commands.ts.
Until then, invocation returns a structured not_enabled error
(octo.enabled: false, per OCTO-DEC-027) or not_implemented (enabled
but no handler attached). Attach semantics live on the octo handler
per OCTO-DEC-032, not in channel bindings.

No behavior change for octo.enabled: false deployments beyond /octo
appearing in /commands listings and autocomplete.

Draft authored against upstream commit 9ece252.

